            {
              "id": "IC_kwDOFcwZ1c5mLDop",
              "body": "@ocfnash Thanks for the review. One of my frustration with this PR is that the same result is true for [Basis.parallelepiped](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Haar/OfBasis.html#Basis.parallelepiped), that is: \r\n```lean\r\nexample [Fintype ι] [DecidableEq ι] (b : Basis ι ℝ (ι → ℝ)) :\r\n    volume (b.parallelepiped) = ENNReal.ofReal |(Matrix.of b).det|\r\n```\r\nbut I was not able to find a nice way to deduce one from the other. Indeed, the quickest way I found to prove the result for `Basis.parallelepiped` is to redo essentially the proof (so I saved this result for another PR if needed). \r\n\r\nMore generally, I think it is still lacking a good mechanism to connect `Basis.parallelepiped` and `Zspan.fundamentalDomain`...\r\n",
              "createdAt": "2023-09-11T16:01:14Z",
              "author": {
                "login": "xroblot"
              }
            },
